<subSubSection pageId="102" pageNumber="380" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="102.[180,1388,295,1191]" pageId="102" pageNumber="380">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[183,541,886,915]" pageId="102" pageNumber="380">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Critically Endangered on The IUCN Red Last. Recent efforts to capture La Guarda Deermice led to conclusion that two of the three subspecies (harbisoni and mejiae) are extinct and that nominate 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Townsend" authorityYear="1912" box="[1093,1194,960,993]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Peromyscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="102" pageNumber="380" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="guardia">guardia</taxonomicName>
may be close to extinction.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
